options.name: -d
tip: display time described by STRING, not 'now'

options.name: -f
tip: like --date; once for each line of DATEFILE

options.name: -I
tip:
U: -I|--iso-8601 [<FMT>]
output date/time in ISO 8601 format.
FMT='date' for date only (the default)
'hours', 'minutes', 'seconds', or 'ns' for date and time to the indicated precision.

options.name: -R
tip: output date and time in RFC 5322 format.

options.name: --rfc-3339
tip:
U: --rfc-3339 <FMT>
output date/time in RFC 3339 format.
FMT='date', 'seconds', or 'ns' for date and time to the indicated precision.
Example: 2006-08-14 02:34:56-06:00

options.name: --debug
options.tip: annotate the parsed date, and warn about questionable usage to stderr

options.name: -r
tip: display the last modification time of FILE

options.name: -u
options.tip: print or set Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)

description: Print or set the system date and time.
